The paper deals with the task of aggregating search results in an E-commerce environment, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of reinforcement learning to learn from user feedback suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the formulation of a slot filling process, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the goal of improving user satisfaction suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
